M. balsamina is important in producing nutrients supplements due its high protein and fat values with low fiber content (
Bakare et al., 2010; 
Costa et al., 2010; 
Roškar and Lušin, 2012; 
Ghosh, 2014; 
Madala et al., 2014; 
Talukdar and Hossain, 2014; 
Abegunde et al., 2018). The leaves of 
M. balsamina are an important source of nutrients, including 17 amino acids (
Cohen et al., 1998; 
Hassan and Umar, 2006; 
Costa et al., 2010; 
Semenya and Potgieter, 2015). 
M. balsamina leaves are mixed with peanuts and honey and used as a meat sauce (
Dellavalle et al., 2011; 
Oronje et al., 2012; 
Sen and Batra, 2012; 
Fongod et al., 2014; 
Bulbul, 2016; 
Poyraz and Derdovski, 2016; 
Mostafa et al., 2018).
